FBIS4-42715 "drweu109__a94026" FBIS-WEU-94-109-A Daily Report 07 June 1994 ANNEX Switzerland Reliability of Goesgen Nuclear Plant Emphasized Reliability of Goesgen Nuclear Plant Emphasized BR0606121894 Bern ATSA/SDAA Database in French 1604 GMT 3 Jun 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY BR0606121894 Bern ATSA/SDAA Database French BFN [Article signed DT/WI/PI: "Maintenance of Goesgen Nuclear Plant -- One-Third of Fuel Elements To Be Changed"] [Text] Goesgen, 3 Jun (ATS) -- The maintenance of the Goesgen Nuclear Plant will start on Saturday [4 June]. One-third of the fuel elements will be changed and many fucntions will be performed. The production of electricity will resume in July, according to a press release issued by the plant's management on Friday. The plant's production reached 98.8 percent of capacity during the last 335 days of the cycle, amounting to 7.382 trillion kWh. This represents 15 percent of Switzerland's electricity needs. These "remarkable" figures are due to the plant's excellent condition and reliability, according to the press release.
